      • getRepositoryFile

        public CommandRepository getRepositoryFile()
        Gets the repository file which was set on this command. The repository can be set either by the creator of the command or by the ExecutionCommandWrapper when it is about to execute the command.
        Returns:
        the repository file that is to be written.
        See Also:
        setRepositoryFile(CommandRepository)

      • setRepositoryFile

        public void setRepositoryFile(CommandRepository repository)
        Sets the CommandRepository which will be sent down to the agent instructing it on which repository file to create on the host. In most cases, it is not necessary to set this file since the ExecutionCommandWrapper will set it in the event that it is missing. In fact, it is only appropriate to set this file in the following cases:
        • When distributing a repository to hosts in preparation for upgrade. This is because the service/component desired stack is not pointing to the new repository yet
        • If the command does not contain a host or service/component>
        Parameters:
        repository - the command repository instance.

      • setComponentVersions

        public void setComponentVersions(Cluster cluster)
                          throws org.apache.ambari.server.AmbariException
        Used to set a map of {service -> { component -> version}}. This is necessary when performing an upgrade to correct build paths of required binaries. This method will only set the version information for a component if:
        • The component advertises a version
        • The repository for the component has been resolved and the version can be trusted
        Parameters:
        cluster - the cluster from which to build the map
        Throws:
        org.apache.ambari.server.AmbariException
